17 Further provided that, relating to dedicated
18 hours, effective July 1, 2026, the
19 Developmental Disabilities Administration
20 (DDA) within the Maryland Department of
21 Health (MDH) shall implement the
22 following policy when implementing cost
23 containment action that enforces dedicated
24 hours policy. Dedicated hours may be
25 accessed when the participant has an
26 assessed medical or behavioral need and an
27 approved behavioral support plan or
28 nursing care plan that justifies the need, or
29 a daytime residential support need as
30 described below. This policy is intended to
31 ensure that, in all other circumstances,
32 such as community integration,
33 appointments, and other circumstances
34 that do not meet the assessed need criteria,
35 shared hours are exhausted before
36 dedicated hours are accessed. Dedicated
37 hours may support more than one
38 participant only when doing so meets each
39 participant’s assessed needs, and the
40 participants are retired, transitioning
41 between meaningful day services,
42 recovering from a health condition, or
43 receiving fewer than 30 hours of
44 meaningful day services per week.

120 SENATE BILL 282
1 DDA will approve dedicated hours without
2 considering the use of shared hours when:
3 (1) the participant has an assessed
4 behavioral need and an approved
5 Behavior Support Plan
6 documenting the need for a 1:1 or
7 2:1 staff–to–participant ratio
8 necessary to support the person
9 with specific behavioral needs; or
10 (2) the participant has an assessed
11 medical need and an approved
12 Nursing Care Plan documenting
13 the need for a 1:1 or 2:1
14 staff–to–participant ratio necessary
15 to support the person with specific
16 health and safety needs; or
17 (3) the participant needs daytime
18 residential support due to
19 retirement, transitioning from one
20 meaningful day service to another,
21 recovery from a serious health
22 condition, or receiving less than 30
23 hours of meaningful day services,
24 and has an approved
25 person–centered plan that
26 documents the assessed need for
27 support.
28 MDH, DDA, or its designee shall provide
29 mandatory, advanced training on
30 dedicated hours to its staff (including
31 Headquarters and regional offices),
32 Coordinator of Community Services
33 agencies, and a representative from each
34 community provider of residential services.
35 This training will include, but is not limited
36 to, detailing DDA’s federal and State
37 approval criteria, its enforcement of federal
38 requirements, and its utilization reviews of
39 shared hours.
40 DDA shall update all policy guidance and
41 manuals to be consistent with this policy by

