10 submits the second of four quarterly hiring
11 and attrition reports to the budget
12 committees. The reports shall include a
13 breakdown of all hires and separations for
14 each of the three months in question by
15 category of employee (correctional officer,
16 community supervision agent, or
17 administrative employee) and by reason for
18 separation. The report shall also include
19 narrative summarizing all hiring events
20 and changes to the hiring process that
21 occurred during the quarter; the quantity,
22 type, and cost of bonuses disbursed; as well
23 as overall applications received, tested, and
24 interviewed. The first report shall be
25 submitted to the budget committees no
26 later than October 1, 2026, the second
27 report shall be submitted to the budget
28 committees no later than January 1, 2027,
29 the third report shall be submitted to the
30 budget committees no later than April 1,
31 2027, and the fourth report shall be
32 submitted to the budget committees no
33 later than July 1, 2027. The budget
34 committees shall have 45 days from the
