40 this appropriation shall be for the purchase
41 of textbooks or computer hardware and
42 software and other electronically delivered
43 learning materials as permitted for loan to
44 students in eligible nonpublic schools with
45 a maximum distribution of $65 per eligible
46 nonpublic school student for participating

180 SENATE BILL 282
1 schools, except that at schools where from
2 20% to 40% of the students are eligible for
3 the free or reduced price lunch program
4 there shall be a distribution of $95 per
5 student and at schools where more than
6 40% of the students are eligible for the free
7 or reduced–price lunch program there shall
8 be a distribution of $155 per student. To be
9 eligible to participate, a nonpublic school
10 shall:
11 (1) Hold a certificate of approval from
12 or be registered with the State
13 Board of Education;
14 (2) Not charge a net tuition average,
15 defined as a school’s total tuition
16 revenue divided by its student
17 enrollment, that is greater than the
18 statewide average per pupil
19 expenditure by the local education
20 agencies, as calculated by the
21 department, with appropriate
22 exceptions for special education
23 students as determined by the
24 department including those
25 attending schools with nonpublic
26 placements;
27 (3) Comply with Title VI of the Civil
28 Rights Act of 1964, as amended;
29 and
30 (4) Submit its student handbook or
31 other written policy related to
32 student admissions to the
33 Maryland State Department of
