9 appropriation for the purpose of general administration within program E00A01.01
10 Executive Direction – Office of the Comptroller may not be expended until the Office of the
11 Comptroller, in collaboration with the Department of Budget and Management, submits a
12 report that identifies, for each funding reversion to the Dedicated Purpose Account (DPA)
13 for fiscal 2021 through 2025, the purpose as expressed in the appropriating language to the
14 extent practical and the budget amendment number that authorized the transfer of funds.
15 The report shall be submitted by July 15, 2026, and the budget committees shall have 45
16 days from the date of the receipt of the report to review and comment. Funds restricted
17 pending the receipt of a report may not be transferred by budget amendment or otherwise
18 to any other purpose and shall revert to the General Fund if the report is not submitted to
19 the budget committees. It is the intent of the General Assembly that the Comptroller of
20 Maryland, in annual fiscal year–end closeout reports beginning with the fiscal 2026 report,
21 identify the budget amendment of origin for funds returned to the DPA or the budget bill
22 purpose for which it was appropriated.
