SENATE BILL 282 389
1 AMENDMENTS TO SENATE BILL 282 / HOUSE BILL 390
2 (First Reading File Bill)
3 Amendment No.1:
4 On page 11, after line 7 insert:
5 “To provide a grant to local governments.
6 Baltimore City.....................$8,000,000”
7 Clarifies the purpose of grant funding in the Board of Public Works.
8 Amendment No. 2:
9 On page 13, in line 8, strike “$100,000,000” and replace it with “$70,000,000”. On
10 page 44, in line 33, strike “$20,000,000” and replace it with “$17,000,000”.
11 Revises the contingent appropriation language for the Maryland Energy Administration and
12 the Department of General Services to reflect utilization of special funds currently allowable
13 under the Strategic Energy Investment Fund. $30 million for MEA’s post–Investment Tax
14 Credit solar incentives, and a $3 million portion of the $20 million DGS solar on state
15 property initiative, will be funded with Regional Greenhouse Gas Initiative funds instead of
16 alternative compliance payments to allow a change in the fund sourcing for General Fund
17 relief from the Strategic Energy Investment Fund.
18 Amendment No. 3:
19 On page 25, strike lines 17 through 23.
20 Removes the contingent language on federal funds in the Maryland Department of
21 Emergency Management to reflect the withdrawal of the related BRFA provision. The federal
22 funds are directly reduced in item 5, where general funds are added. The withdrawal of the
23 BRFA provision will result in the failure of the contingency on the special funds in lines 5
24 through 11 on the same page, and therefore will be reduced.
25 Amendment No. 4:
26 On page 119, in line 20 after “Appropriation” insert, “, provided that this
27 appropriation shall be reduced by $250,000 contingent upon the enactment of legislation
28 modifying the mandate for the Title IX Representation Fund.” In line 21, after
29 “Appropriation”, insert “, provided that $250,000 of this appropriation is contingent upon
30 the enactment of legislation modifying the mandate for the Title IX Representation Fund.”
31 Add contingent language in the Maryland Higher Education Commission to utilize the Title
32 IX Representation Fund’s balance in FY 2027 in lieu of General Funds.
33 Amendment No. 5:
34 On page 124, in line 10, replace “807,975,435” and with “$802,975,435”.
35 To reflect the removal of duplicate funding for the Maryland Clean Energy Center’s Climate
36 Catalytic Capital Fund, consistent with Item 38 of this Supplemental Budget.

390 SENATE BILL 282
1 Amendment No. 6:
